metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #77
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
Made with love by culla using p5.js

metadata.name: 10SCII #390
metadata.description:
10SCII is my take on the famous 10 PRINT program.

10 PRINT CHR$(205.5+RND(1)); : GOTO 10 is a single line program that produces a simple but visually appealing set of forward and backward slashes.

This project riffs on the original idea by removing the vertical space between lines and widening the horizontal gap. This changes the produced pieces from a maze of slashes into a series of towers. This is then rendered and animated as ASCII.

Visit https://10print.org/ to learn more about the original program that inspired this piece.

metadata.name: The Streamline #62
metadata.description:
Form, an essential aspect in architectural design, refers to the shape, structure and arrangement of spaces or objects. Witnessing how forms work in a space can also be a transcendental experience, where one can sense the presence of a form, not only seeing it.

As there are many ways to create it, Form can appear as an internal structure, as an external shape of a two dimensional plane that envelopes a three dimensional mass, or a repetition of a two dimensional shape that stacks on an axis and moves to a certain direction. With so many ways to create shape, there is no law dictating that shape has to be rigid. And this is where Milunic and Gehry's design for the Dancing House comes in as an inspiration for this work.

A change in the political axis from one of a regime to a parliamentary democracy was what influenced the architects to juxtapose two different energies together. With its dynamic and static shapes in tandem, Dancing House is one iconic proof that form can also be pliable and animated.

------------
Press [s] to save captured image
------------
It may take a few seconds to render, depending on the device.
works better with chrome

created using WEBGL on p5.js
dirbots - Feb23

metadata.name: lilium #28
metadata.description:
lilium is a remix of my piece for day 9 of genuary 2023, prompt "Plants". it uses a series of force-directed graph layouts to produce a bouquet of flowers. inspired by Jared Tarbell's Happy Place.

press "c" to capture a screenshot at the current resolution. if you'd like a screenshot at a particular resolution, you can press "r" and a prompt will appear that will let you select a fixed resolution. you can either provide a single number like "1080" or a series of two numbers like "1080x2160". you can also provide a fixed resolution in the url with the "?resolution=..."

metadata.name: All The Way #187
metadata.description:
"All the Way" is a visually stunning and dynamic generative art piece that is sure to make a striking addition to any art collection. Created using the programming language p5js, this artwork is truly one of a kind and cannot be replicated.

The vibrant colors, fluid shapes, and dynamic movement in "All the Way" make it an ideal centerpiece for any space. The constantly shifting shapes and colors create a sense of energy and motion that will draw the eye and captivate the viewer. This piece is perfect for anyone who loves abstract art or is looking for something unique and eye-catching to add to their collection.

Additionally, the theme of "All the Way" is one that is sure to resonate with many people. The artwork represents the flow of life, the power of creativity, and the endless possibilities that exist in the world around us. This makes it an ideal choice for anyone who values personal growth, exploration, and a sense of adventure.

Whether you're an art collector, an art enthusiast, or simply someone who appreciates beautiful and thought-provoking art, "All the Way" is a must-have addition to your collection. With its dynamic and abstract style, this piece is sure to spark conversations and inspire new ideas. Don't miss out on the chance to own a truly unique and captivating artwork that you will enjoy for years to come!

To save image press "s"
To save image in high quality add &print=2 or &print=3 in the live URL then press "s".

Note: Image can take a minute to render.

Created using p5js and p5js pattern
Created By Winston
Feb 2023

p5.js


Interact with the canvas via your mouse.
------------
Press 'i' -> info.
(📱Press and hold for 1s -> info.)
------------
Press 's' (fullscreen) -> png.
